You are here: Salesforce Help -> Docs -> Analytics
Create an app to organize and contain any combination of lenses, dashboards, and datasets. 
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

Click Create on the home page, select App, click Create Blank App, then Continue.
Enter the name of your app and click Create.
Your app is created and displayed in a new tab. You can now save lenses, dashboards, and datasets in the app.
App names have a 40 character limit.

Add a description to your app's purpose and contents.
Click the pencil icon in the description field, type a description, and it will be automatically saved.
Change the app's default icon by selecting an icon from the gallery, which will be automatically saved.

IMPORTANT: When users are deactivated, they lose share and delete access to all apps they manage.
title: Creating Salesforce CRM Analytics Apps
